The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically the Induced Disjoint Paths problem. This problem is related to graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, and cs.CC. The paper's focus on circular-arc graphs suggests that it may be more likely to be classified under cs.CG or cs.DM, which deal with computational geometry and discrete mathematics, respectively. However, the paper's algorithmic approach and linear-time complexity may also make it relevant to cs.DS, cs.GT, or cs.CC, which cover data structures, graph theory, and computational complexity, respectively.
